noRecentPolicySyncCount.description: Number of ChromeOS devices have not synced policies in the past 28 days.

osVersionNotCompliantCount.description: Number of devices whose OS version is not compliant.

noRecentUserActivityCount.description: Number of ChromeOS devices that have not seen any user activity in the past 28 days.

deviceId.description: Output only. Represents the graphics card device id.

adapter.description: Output only. Adapter name. Example: Mesa DRI Intel(R) UHD Graphics 620 (Kabylake GT2).

driverVersion.description: Output only. Version of the GPU driver.

updateState.description: Output only. Current state of the os update.
enumDescriptions: OS has started download on device.
Device needs reboot to finish upload.

newRequestedPlatformVersion.description: Output only. New requested platform version from the pending updated kiosk app.

newPlatformVersion.description: Output only. New platform version of the os image being downloaded and applied. It is only set when update status is OS_IMAGE_DOWNLOAD_IN_PROGRESS or OS_UPDATE_NEED_REBOOT. Note this could be a dummy "0.0.0.0" for OS_UPDATE_NEED_REBOOT status for some edge cases, e.g. update engine is restarted without a reboot.

lastUpdateCheckTime.description: Output only. Timestamp of the last update check.

lastUpdateTime.description: Output only. Timestamp of the last successful update.

lastRebootTime.description: Output only. Timestamp of the last reboot.

GoogleChromeManagementV1OsUpdateStatus.description: Contains information regarding the current OS update status. * This field is telemetry information and this will change over time as the device is utilized. * Data for this field is controlled via policy: [ReportDeviceOsUpdateStatus](https://chromeenterprise.google/policies/#ReportDeviceOsUpdateStatus) * Data Collection Frequency: Only at Upload * Default Data Reporting Frequency: 3 hours - Policy Controlled: Yes * Cache: If the device is offline, the collected data is stored locally, and will be reported when the device is next online: No * Reported for affiliated users only: N/A

batteryInfo.description: Output only. Information on battery specs for the device.

customer.description: Output only. Google Workspace Customer whose enterprise enrolled the device.

name.description: Output only. Resource name of the device.

orgUnitId.description: Output only. Organization unit ID of the device.

graphicsInfo.description: Output only. Contains information regarding Graphic peripherals for the device.

thunderboltInfo.description: Output only. Information on Thunderbolt bus.

cpuInfo.description: Output only. Information regarding CPU specs for the device.

osUpdateStatus.description: Output only. Contains relevant information regarding ChromeOS update status.

networkDiagnosticsReport.description: Output only. Network diagnostics collected periodically.

batteryStatusReport.description: Output only. Battery reports collected periodically.

serialNumber.description: Output only. Device serial number. This value is the same as the Admin Console's Serial Number in the ChromeOS Devices tab.

storageInfo.description: Output only. Information of storage specs for the device.

storageStatusReport.description: Output only. Storage reports collected periodically.

memoryStatusReport.description: Output only. Memory status reports collected periodically sorted decreasing by report_time.

deviceId.description: Output only. The unique Directory API ID of the device. This value is the same as the Admin Console's Directory API ID in the ChromeOS Devices tab

networkStatusReport.description: Output only. Network specs collected periodically.

audioStatusReport.description: Output only. Audio reports collected periodically sorted in a decreasing order of report_time.

cpuStatusReport.description: Output only. CPU status reports collected periodically sorted in a decreasing order of report_time.

bootPerformanceReport.description: Output only. Boot performance reports of the device.

graphicsStatusReport.description: Output only. Graphics reports collected periodically.

memoryInfo.description: Output only. Information regarding memory specs for the device.

GoogleChromeManagementV1TelemetryDevice.description: Telemetry data collected from a managed device.

totalDiskBytes.description: The total space for user data storage in the device in bytes.

availableDiskBytes.description: The available space for user data storage in the device in bytes.

GoogleChromeManagementV1StorageInfo.description: Status data for storage. * This field is telemetry information and this will change over time as the device is utilized. * Data for this field is controlled via policy: [ReportDeviceStorageStatus](https://chromeenterprise.google/policies/#ReportDeviceStorageStatus) * Data Collection Frequency: Only at Upload * Default Data Reporting Frequency: 3 hours - Policy Controlled: Yes * Cache: If the device is offline, the collected data is stored locally, and will be reported when the device is next online: No * Reported for affiliated users only: N/A

nextPageToken.description: Token to specify next page in the list.

devices.description: Telemetry devices returned in the response.

appType.description: Output only. Type of the app.

appInstallType.description: Output only. How the app was installed.

permissions.description: Output only. Permissions of the installed app.

disabled.description: Output only. Whether the app is disabled.

browserDeviceCount.description: Output only. Count of browser devices with this app installed.

homepageUri.description: Output only. Homepage uri of the installed app.

enumDescriptions: Generally for extensions and Chrome apps.
appSource.description: Output only. Source of the installed app.

appId.description: Output only. Unique identifier of the app. For Chrome apps and extensions, the 32-character id (e.g. ehoadneljpdggcbbknedodolkkjodefl). For Android apps, the package name (e.g. com.evernote).

displayName.description: Output only. Name of the installed app.

description.description: Output only. Description of the installed app.

osUserCount.description: Output only. Count of ChromeOS users with this app installed.

systemRamFreeBytes.description: Output only. Amount of free RAM in bytes (unreliable due to Garbage Collection).

reportTime.description: Output only. The timestamp in milliseconds representing time at which this report was sampled.

sampleFrequency.description: Output only. Frequency the report is sampled.

pageFaults.description: Output only. Number of page faults during this collection

GoogleChromeManagementV1MemoryStatusRepo.description: Contains samples of memory status reports. * This field is telemetry information and this will change over time as the device is utilized. * Data for this field is controlled via policy: [ReportDeviceMemoryInfo](https://chromeenterprise.google/policies/#ReportDeviceMemoryInfo) * Data Collection Frequency: Only at upload, SystemRamFreeByes is collected every 10 minutes * Default Data Reporting Frequency: Every 3 hours - Policy Controlled: Yes * Cache: If the device is offline, the collected data is stored locally, and will be reported when the device is next online: No * Reported for affiliated users only: N/A

GoogleChromeManagementV1NetworkStatusRep.description: State of visible/configured networks. * This field is telemetry information and this will change over time as the device is utilized. * Data for this field is controlled via policy: [ReportNetworkStatus](https://chromeenterprise.google/policies/#ReportNetworkStatus) * Data Collection Frequency: 60 minutes * Default Data Reporting Frequency: 3 hours - Policy Controlled: Yes * Cache: If the device is offline, the collected data is stored locally, and will be reported when the device is next online: Yes * Reported for affiliated users only: Yes

sampleFrequency.description: Output only. Frequency the report is sampled.

transmissionPowerDbm.description: Output only. Transmission power measured in decibels.

wifiLinkQuality.description: Output only. Wifi link quality. Value ranges from [0, 70]. 0 indicates no signal and 70 indicates a strong signal.

encryptionOn.description: Output only. Whether the wifi encryption key is turned off.

signalStrengthDbm.description: Output only. Signal strength for wireless networks measured in decibels.

receivingBitRateMbps.description: Output only. Receiving bit rate measured in Megabits per second.

reportTime.description: Output only. Time at which the network state was reported.

connectionState.description: Output only. Current connection state of the network.
enumDescriptions: The network is connected and internet connectivity is available.
The network is connected and not in a detected portal state, but internet connectivity may not be available.
The network is connected but a portal state was detected. Internet connectivity may be limited.
The network is in the process of connecting.

wifiPowerManagementEnabled.description: Output only. Wifi power management enabled

transmissionBitRateMbps.description: Output only. Transmission bit rate measured in Megabits per second.

hostMatch.description: Output only. This can contain very specific hosts, or patterns like "*.com" for instance.

iconUri.description: Output only. A link to an image that can be used as an icon for the product.

appId.description: Output only. Unique store identifier for the app. Example: "gmbmikajjgmnabiglmofipeabaddhgne" for the Save to Google Drive Chrome extension.

requestCount.description: Output only. Total count of requests for this app.

latestRequestTime.description: Output only. The timestamp of the most recently made request for this app.

detailUri.description: Output only. The uri for the detail page of the item.

GoogleChromeManagementV1ChromeAppRequest.description: Details of an app installation request.

GoogleChromeManagementV1BatteryInfo.description: Information about the battery. * This field provides device information, which is static and will not change over time. * Data for this field is controlled via policy: [ReportDevicePowerStatus](https://chromeenterprise.google/policies/#ReportDevicePowerStatus) * Data Collection Frequency: Only at Upload * Default Data Reporting Frequency: 3 hours - Policy Controlled: Yes * Cache: If the device is offline, the collected data is stored locally, and will be reported when the device is next online: No * Reported for affiliated users only: N/A

designMinVoltage.description: Output only. Designed minimum output voltage (mV)

manufactureDate.description: Output only. The date the battery was manufactured.

technology.description: Output only. Technology of the battery. Example: Li-ion
